util

Interface ObjectStore

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    NamingService, ObjectStoreStub

    public interface ObjectStore
    ObjectStore is an interface that describes how to store and recover RemoteObj instances for project-wide consultation.
    See Also:
    RemoteObj, Clique

    • Method Detail

      • getObject

        java.util.Optional<RemoteObj> getObject(java.lang.String name,
                                        long tag)
        Get an object reference by unique-name and tag.
        Parameters:
        name - An unique string identifying a set of objects.
        tag - The tag of a specific object in that set.
        Returns:
        The reference or empty if it does not exist in the store.

      • getObject

        java.util.Optional<RemoteObj> getObject(java.lang.String name)
        Get an object reference by unique-name.
        Parameters:
        name - An unique string identifying a set of objects.
        Returns:
        The reference to a random object of that set, or empty if no reference exists.

      • insertObject

        boolean insertObject(java.lang.String name,
                     RemoteObj ro)
        Insert an object into a unique-name's set.

        Can be used to store objects whose functionality is independant of the actual machine in which they are located and any such object is capable of serving the same kinds of requests.

        Parameters:
        name - Unique-name under which to insert the reference.
        ro - Reference to insert under name.
        Returns:
        whether the insertion succeeded.
